    <text>
        <div facs="#eSc_textblock_183da727">
            <lb />
            <hi rendition="#c">
                <hi rendition="#i">
                    <hi rendition="#u">
                        <seg xml:id="immortals" ana="#immortality" resp="#np" type="topic">
                            The Instrument of the Immortals
                        </seg>
                        <note type="editorial" ref="#immortals" resp="#np">
                            The slogan was originally invented by
                            <persName>Raymond Rubicam</persName> in 1919, who
                            referred to the long-lasting history of Steinway pianos.
                            Nevertheless, the "immortality" theme is analysed 
                            here, since the slogan gets reinterpreted by its 
                            context.
                        </note>
                    </hi>
                </hi>
            </hi>
        </div>
        <div facs="#eSc_dummyblock_">
            <lb />
            <head>
                <orgName>Steinway</orgName><lb />Welte<lb />Grand
            </head>
            <lb />The Welte-Mignon, which<lb />
            <seg ana="#exact_reproduction" resp="#np" type="topic">
                reproduces absolutely the
                <lb />Artists' original renderings
            </seg>,
            <lb />retains its position amongst<lb />the
            World's foremost and<lb />greatest reproducing instru-<lb />ments.<lb />The Steinway
            Welte is<lb />made also as a self-contained<lb />upright piano. Welte cabi-<lb />nets
            when desired can be<lb />supplied separately for at-<lb />tachment to any pianoforte.<lb />Renderings
            by: </div>
